HEADWORD: Halesia
<hw>Ha*le"si*a</hw> <pr>(h⟦adot⟧*l⟦emac⟧"zh⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of
American shrubs containing several species, called <altname>snowdrop
trees</altname>, or silver-bell trees. They have showy, white flowers,
drooping on slender pedicels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

